headline: Netflix Stock Is Falling. This Is Overshadowing the Streamer’s Earnings Beat.
summary: Netflix  issued softer-than-expected margin guidance late Tuesday, overshadowing higher fourth-quarter earnings than expected.  The video streamer reported a fourth-quarter profit of 56 cents a share, as revenue climbed almost 18% from a year ago to $12.05 billion.  Analysts were looking for earnings of 55 cents a share on revenue of $11.97 billion, according to FactSet.
